{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CdH818N4vHuKmfQ8FJLYT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fixed. The bug was a cache-key collision in `src/userService.js`.\n\n**Root cause:** The cache key was `users:${opts.team}` — it ignored the `includeArchived` flag. So a request that asked for archived users (`includeArchived: true`) would cache the full list under `users:<team>`, and the picker's subsequent request for `includeArchived: false` would get that same cached entry back, archived users included. The 60s cache TTL explains why refreshing after a minute clears it: the poisoned entry simply expires.\n\n**Fix:** Include `includeArchived` in the cache key so the two variants get separate entries:\n\n```js\nconst key = `users:${opts.team}:${opts.includeArchived ? \"1\" : \"0\"}`;\n```\n\n`npm test` passes (1/1)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2331,"cache_read_input_tokens":20685,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2331},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"36d0a7b3-fc8a-4005-8a45-d4eab3d507c0","uuid":"a1b24a93-2c00-4717-9d8a-2c716b1b70c3","timestamp":"2026-07-22T12:47:54.558Z","request_id":"req_011CdH8175RcxCRUVjJgr5tf"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":20294,"duration_api_ms":19166,"ttft_ms":3966,"ttft_stream_ms":1499,"time_to_request_ms":23,"num_turns":5,"result":"Fixed. The bug was a cache-key collision in `src/userService.js`.\n\n**Root cause:** The cache key was `users:${opts.team}` — it ignored the `includeArchived` flag. So a request that asked for archived users (`includeArchived: true`) would cache the full list under `users:<team>`, and the picker's subsequent request for `includeArchived: false` would get that same cached entry back, archived users included. The 60s cache TTL explains why refreshing after a minute clears it: the poisoned entry simply expires.\n\n**Fix:** Include `includeArchived` in the cache key so the two variants get separate entries:\n\n```js\nconst key = `users:${opts.team}:${opts.includeArchived ? \"1\" : \"0\"}`;\n```\n\n`npm test` passes (1/1).","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"36d0a7b3-fc8a-4005-8a45-d4eab3d507c0","total_cost_usd":0.137522,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7779,"cache_read_input_tokens":55854,"output_tokens":1271,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":7779,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-8":{"inputTokens":6,"outputTokens":1271,"cacheReadInputTokens":55854,"cacheCreationInputTokens":7779,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.137522,"contextWindow":1000000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"d9a4ea7d-d4e7-4a2a-848d-7b0b7b4a3742"}
